SIMPLE: stager
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stager
<hw>Sta"ger</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧"j⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A player.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who has long acted on the stage of life; a
practitioner; a person of experience, or of skill derived from long
experience.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧You will find most of the old
<xex>stagers</xex> still stationary there.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A horse used in drawing a stage.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stagery</ent>⟦br⟧
